## Skill Ownership Model

### 1. `docs/astro/project_builder/SKILL.md`

Purpose:

- bootstrap skill
- Astro file discipline
- docs-first rule
- project context verification
- routing to the correct domain skill

This skill must not teach full domain behavior.

It should own:

- mandatory read order
- `astro/brief.md`, `astro/tasks.md`, `astro/status.md`, `astro/record.md`, `astro/journal.md`
- project-context checks
- docs-first workflow
- namespace-first rule as a global safety rule
- routing to the correct specialized skill

It should not own:

- DataNode design
- SimpleTable semantics
- FastAPI design
- workspace design
- job/release semantics
- RBAC semantics
- markets/VFB/instruments semantics

### 2. `docs/astro/data_publishing/data_nodes/SKILL.md`

Purpose:

- all DataNode engineering in one place

It should own:

- DataNode identifiers
- hashing model
- storage vs update hash
- hash namespaces
- dependencies
- `update()` expectations
- metadata
- test patterns
- MultiIndex DataNodes
- asset-indexed DataNodes
- `get_asset_list()`
